{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Per-county ArcGIS parcel REST endpoints. When a geocoded address falls in a covered county, we query that county's authoritative parcel service for the exact polygon — gives true lot square footage instead of OSM guesses.",
    "how_to_add": "Find your county's parcel ArcGIS REST service URL (usually published by the county GIS or assessor), verify it with a live point query, then add an entry below. The pipeline uses it automatically when an address falls in that county's state + ZIP-prefix set. Geometry is requested in WGS84 (EPSG:4326) so we compute area ourselves — no need to know the service's spatial reference.",
    "ordering": "Counties are tried in list order when ZIP prefixes overlap (e.g. St. Louis City before St. Louis County — both claim 631xx). Put the more specific jurisdiction first.",
    "verified": "Every entry below was live-verified with a real point/envelope query on 2026-07-03.",
    "spatial_rel": "Endpoints must support point-in-polygon via geometryType=esriGeometryPoint + spatialRel=esriSpatialRelIntersects, and envelope queries via esriGeometryEnvelope."
  },
